    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>An old question, but I also have two methods.  </p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>For a fixed (predefined) length:  </p>\n\n<pre><code>    public static String fill(String text) {\n        if (text.length() &gt;= 10)\n            return text;\n        else\n            return \"0000000000\".substring(text.length()) + text;\n    }\n</code></pre>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>For a variable length:  </p>\n\n<pre><code>    public static String fill(String text, int size) {\n        StringBuilder builder = new StringBuilder(text);\n        while (builder.length() &lt; size) {\n            builder.append('0');\n        }\n        return builder.toString();\n    }\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
