    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>To format String use </p>\n\n<pre><code>import org.apache.commons.lang.StringUtils;\n\npublic class test {\n\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n\n        String result = StringUtils.leftPad(\"wrwer\", 10, \"0\");\n        System.out.println(\"The String : \" + result);\n\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Output : The String : 00000wrwer</p>\n\n<p>Where the first argument is the string to be formatted, Second argument is the length of the desired output length and third argument is the char with which the string is to be padded.</p>\n\n<p>Use the link to download the jar <code>http://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-lang/download_lang.cgi</code></p>\n"
