    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>The solution by Satish is very good among the expected answers. I wanted to make it more general by adding variable n to format string instead of 10 chars.</p>\n\n<pre><code>int maxDigits = 10;\nString str = \"129018\";\nString formatString = \"%\"+n+\"s\";\nString str2 = String.format(formatString, str).replace(' ', '0');\nSystem.out.println(str2);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This will work in most situations</p>\n"
